Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement
Rule 2     program -> LABEL COLUMN NEWLINE
Rule 3     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA register NEWLINE
Rule 4     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register NEWLINE
Rule 5     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA IMMEDIATE NEWLINE
Rule 6     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA IMMEDIATE NEWLINE
Rule 7     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA LABEL NEWLINE
Rule 8     statement -> OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA LABEL NEWLINE
Rule 9     statement -> OPCODE LABEL NEWLINE
Rule 10    statement -> OPCODE register NEWLINE
Rule 11    register -> REGISTER
Rule 12    statement -> NEWLINE

Terminals, with rules where they appear

COLUMN               : 2
COMMA                : 3 3 4 5 5 6 7 8 8
IMMEDIATE            : 5 6
LABEL                : 2 7 8 9
NEWLINE              : 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 10 12
OPCODE               : 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 10
REGISTER             : 11
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

program              : 0
register             : 3 3 3 4 4 5 5 6 7 8 8 10
statement            : 1

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . program
    (1) program -> . statement
    (2) program -> . LABEL COLUMN NEWLINE
    (3) statement -> . OPCODE register COMMA register COMMA register NEWLINE
    (4) statement -> . OPCODE register COMMA register NEWLINE
